\section{1849-50 15c}

During May 1850 the rates for tranmission of letters was changed. The internal rate up to 7 \half grams increased from 20 centimes to 25 centimes, effective from 1st July 1850. The internal rate for Paris was 15 centimes (Fig.~\ref{local}) and the internal town rate (except Paris) 10 centimes.

Only 3.3 million copies of the 15 centimes value were printed using two plates, so it is rare even as a single stamp. It exists in various shades of green the listed ones being (a) yellow-green, b) green, c) dark green and d) deep bottle green.

